attachments.title: Magic Leap’s and King’s deals pave way for big jump in 2016 game transactions
attachments.text: Augmented reality glasses firm Magic Leap confirmed today that it has raised $793.5 million from Alibaba Group and other investors. Together with the expected closing of the $5.9 billion acquisition of King by Activision Blizzard, the Magic Leap funding could do wonders for game-related deal activity in 2016.
